{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"12dea983-7a70-4534-b4e2-50c52e03edd9","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0, you just need to **remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Remove this line (or set to false): -->\n    <!-- <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest> -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Why this is enough:** Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.4+, Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the **default** runner. Setting `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` was opting you back into the legacy runner. Removing it gives you the new platform automatically.\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n\n| Area | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| CLI | Use `dotnet test` as before, but `--filter` syntax may differ slightly |\n| Extensions | VSTest adapters are replaced by Microsoft.Testing.Platform extensions |\n| `.runsettings` | Still supported, but platform-specific config uses `testconfig.json` |\n| TRX output | Add `<EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>` is implicit; for TRX use `--results-directory` |\n\n**If you use CI or `dotnet test` flags**, verify your scripts still work — most common options (`--filter`, `--logger trx`) are supported but some niche VSTest switches may need updating.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cc45689a-1df6-4674-83e6-1dc197cd1d45","outputTokens":362,"requestId":"BC45:DC2FD:1CD75F1:1FE9950:69FA9058"},"id":"ec1f8f21-815d-439e-a6b8-4e25e8377149","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:50:45.395Z","parentId":"68deb3cc-4756-45e2-8297-983256582472"}
